Hi guys,

I think the title should be ''Supported Accommodation Enquiries'' rather than ''Contact Us''.

Also the first line where it reads ''Please contact us on (02) 9808 9601 for all disability enquiries or alternatively, fill out the below form and we will get back to you as soon as possible.'' Change that to read ''To enquire about one of our accommodation vacancies, simply fill out the form below so we can be sure to best serve your needs, and one of our friendly staff will be in touch soon. Alternatively, you can contact us on (02) 9808 9601.''

We want users to fill out the form if possible, so we can better track the number of conversions, but don't want to lose them if they are put off by the form.

Kind regards,

Trudy.

Hi Heath,

Hope you are well.

As Trudy mentioned to you earlier, we are working on upgrading a few things on our Disability section for our website.

Can we please create a new “Contact Us” page dedicated to Disability Services?

Please see attached format of what I would like to see. I would also like the main image to be the below:
https://royalrehab.com.au/wp-content/uploads/NDIS-Disability-Support-Coordination-Sydney.jpg <https://royalrehab.com.au/wp-content/uploads/NDIS-Disability-Support-Coordination-Sydney.jpg>

Can we ensure that all fields are compulsory apart from Funding Details (multiple choice) and Interested In.

Once you create this page, can you please create another page that generates a Thank You message?

Message below:
Thank you for your disability services enquiry. Our team will come back to you as soon possible.

Once this is done, can you please ensure that the Contact Us page is underneath the “Disability Supports & Accommodation” umbrella on the top bar, and that all the Contact Us links on the other Disability pages (Overview, Accommodation, Accommodation Waitlist, Support services, Support coordination) link to this Contact Us page and not the generic Contact Us page?



Any questions, let me know.

Thank you,
Janina
